					<head>Pentateuch</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/sh85118979" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Pentateuch scroll. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="1r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר תורה</title>
							<note>
								<p>A fragment only, beginning with Numbers 8:9, and ending with Numbers 33:52. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 15th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Red leather. </support>
								<extent>17 membranes, 37 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>580</height>
										<width>4510</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>17 membranes, with header/wrapper (572mm long). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Staining and water damage throughout, in patches. </p>
									<p>Dirt, mud, accretions, deliberate erasures. </p>
									<p>Some dark, contracted edges. </p>
									<p>Worming. </p>
									<p>Folds. </p>
									<p>Some abraded surfaces and delamination. </p>
									<p>Ink falking in parts, with losses of text. </p>
									<p>Ink offset on verso.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="37" ruledLines="50 51" writtenLines="50 51">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and stiching of membranes. </p>
									<p>37 columns in total, one to six columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>No tagin on letters. In some fragments ח is arched.</p>
									<p>Special shapes of letters occur: the inverted נ placed before and after Num. 10:35-36, פ&apos; לפוף is frequent. </p>
									<p>Columns generally begin with a new verse. </p>
									<p>Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>The &quot;puncta extraordinaria&quot; placed on the words fixed by masorah. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
